name: The Walking Dead: Dead City
overview: Maggie and Negan travel to post-apocalyptic Manhattan - long ago cut off from the mainland. The crumbling city is filled with the dead and denizens who have made it a world full of anarchy, danger, beauty, and terror.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: In season two, in the growing war for control of Manhattan, Maggie and Negan find themselves trapped on opposite sides. As their paths intertwine, they come to see that the way out for both is more complicated and harrowing than they ever imagined.

episodes.name: Old Acquaintances
episodes.overview: Maggie finds Negan, and they travel to Manhattan; a marshal named Armstrong follows Negan; we meet a quiet young girl named Ginny.

episodes.name: Who's There?
episodes.overview: Maggie and Negan encounter native New Yorkers; Armstrong revisits a trauma; Ginny attempts to adapt to change.

episodes.name: People Are a Resource
episodes.overview: Dark instincts reveal themselves as Maggie and Negan form a strategy; Armstrong is tested; Ginny embarks on a daring journey.

episodes.name: Everybody Wins a Prize
episodes.overview: Maggie and Negan carry out an attack, but not everything unfolds according to plan; Ginny and Armstrong each make unexpected contact with others.

episodes.name: Stories We Tell Ourselves
episodes.overview: Truths are unearthed and motives are revealed as Maggie, Negan and the others travel further into the city's depths.

episodes.name: Doma Smo
episodes.overview: Tensions between Maggie and Negan come to a head; Ginny's search continues; questions arise around Armstrong's path forward.
